            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, add a knob of<strong> butter</strong>, the juice of <strong>half </strong>your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until wilted</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemony</strong> <strong>orzo primavera</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
